base helpers, report types (agents still write JSON reports). The Go code removes: all imperative health check functions (TCP, latency, databases, zombies, backup, disk, respond). The daemon's pourDoctorMolecule in daemon.go already exists as a separate anomaly-triggered path - it should stay (it's for ensureDoltServerRunning anomaly detection). The runDoctorDog periodic path changes to just pour the molecule.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"assignee\":\"gastown/polecats/nux\",\"owner\":\"steve.yegge@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-01T01:57:56Z\",\"created_by\":\"mayor\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-01T23:13:25Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-01T23:13:25Z\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\"}"}
